{"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StateManagement","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ThemingGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusSystem","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/KeyboardShortcuts","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PaletteReference","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ListAndTable","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/LayoutSystem"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit’s preference system enables "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"bottom-up data flow","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": the reverse of environment values. While the environment passes data down from parent to child, preferences let child views publish values that ancestors can observe and react to."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The system mirrors SwiftUI’s preference API and consists of three parts:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"PreferenceKey","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Protocol that defines a named value type with a default and a reduce strategy"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceValues"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Type-safe storage that holds all preference values for a scope"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"PreferenceStorage","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Stack-based collector that manages preference contexts per render pass"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A built-in example is "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey"},{"type":"text","text":": a child view sets "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".navigationTitle(\"Settings\")"},{"type":"text","text":", and the enclosing navigation container reads that preference to render the title bar."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Defining a Preference Key","anchor":"Defining-a-Preference-Key"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A preference key declares what type of value it carries and how multiple values from sibling children are combined:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct CounterKey: PreferenceKey {","    static let defaultValue: Int = 0","","    static func reduce(value: inout Int, nextValue: () -> Int) {","        value += nextValue()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"defaultValue"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Returned when no child has set this preference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"reduce(value:nextValue:)","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Combines values when multiple children set the same key"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"text":" implementation simply takes the last value. Override it when you need additive behavior (summing counts), array collection, or other merge strategies.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Setting a Preference","anchor":"Setting-a-Preference"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Child views publish a preference using the "},{"code":".preference(key:value:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct ItemView: View {","    var body: some View {","        Text(\"Item\")","            .preference(key: CounterKey.self, value: 1)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Under the hood, this wraps the view in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" that calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preferences.setValue(_:forKey:)"},{"type":"text","text":" during rendering. The value is reduced into the current scope using the key’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Observing Preferences","anchor":"Observing-Preferences"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ancestor views react to collected preferences using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".onPreferenceChange(_:perform:)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct ItemList: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","        }","        .onPreferenceChange(CounterKey.self) { totalCount in","            \/\/ totalCount == 3 (three children each set value: 1, additive reduce)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier pushes a new preference context, renders all children (which set their preferences), pops the context, and fires the callback with the accumulated result.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"The Navigation Title Shortcut","anchor":"The-Navigation-Title-Shortcut"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit provides "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey"},{"type":"text","text":" as a built-in preference key with a convenience modifier:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct SettingsPage: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Text(\"App settings go here\")","        }","        .navigationTitle(\"Settings\")","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"NavigationTitleKey","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" uses the default "},{"code":"reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (last value wins), so the deepest child’s title takes precedence.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"How-Preferences-Flow-per-Frame","text":"How Preferences Flow per Frame","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Preferences are collected fresh every frame. Here’s the lifecycle within a single render pass:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reset"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"code":"RenderLoop.render()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"preferences.beginRenderPass()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", clearing all callbacks and resetting the stack to a single empty context","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set"}]},{"type":"text","text":": As the view tree renders top-down, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" views call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setValue(_:forKey:)"},{"type":"text","text":", which reduces values into the current stack frame"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scope"}]},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"code":"OnPreferenceChangeModifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" pushes a new context before rendering its subtree, isolating child preferences","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Collect"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": After the subtree finishes, the modifier pops the context (merging into the parent) and fires the callback with the scoped result","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Discard","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": At the start of the next frame, everything resets: stale preferences never persist"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This per-frame reset ensures preferences always reflect the current view tree. Removed views stop contributing automatically."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Reduce-Strategies","text":"Reduce Strategies","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function determines how multiple children’s values combine. Common patterns:"}]},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Strategy","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Case"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Last value wins"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"value = nextValue()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (default)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Titles, labels: deepest child wins","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additive"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value += nextValue()"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Counting items, summing heights"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Array collection"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"value.append(contentsOf: nextValue())","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Gathering menu items, breadcrumbs","type":"text"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{